"script": "Imagine scooping up a single teaspoon of a dead star. That tiny spoonful would weigh about a billion tons, roughly as much as every car, truck, and ship on Earth combined. It comes from a neutron star, the crushed leftover core of a giant sun. When the star died, gravity squeezed it so hard that the empty space inside its atoms was crushed out completely. Now a ball the size of a city holds more mass than our entire Sun. And if you dropped that spoonful, it would punch straight through the planet.",
